Western Cape Police say an inquest docket has been opened after the body of a woman was found on Table Mountain. Sakina Grimwood (32) from Newlands had been missing since Wednesday. She was a lecturer at Varsity College. Mountain rescue teams used a helicopter to retrieve her body. Police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana says a tour guide found her body near a steep cliff at Platteklip Gorge. “According to information the body was found yesterday afternoon on Table Mountain. A post mortem will be conducted to determine the cause of death.”  